            . I am a <rs id="t18300415-342-viclabel1850" type="occupation">grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-342-victim2827 t18300415-342-viclabel1850"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300415-342-crimeloc1851">Fenchurch-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-342-crimeloc1851" type="placeName" value="Fenchurch-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-342-crimeloc1851" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-342-off1848 t18300415-342-crimeloc1851"></join>. I was engaged with a gentleman at the back part of my premises, and saw Hill pass several times - I then saw him stoop and take this bag of coffee from the door; it was just within the threshold - I went out, and saw Bartlett with it, in the possession of Herdsfield -Hill was running away, but was stopped, and both secured.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-342-person2829">
                  CHARLES 
                  HERDSFIELD
               <interp inst="t18300415-342-person2829" type="surname" value="HERDSFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-342-person2829" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-342-person2829" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw Hill standing at Mr. Roach's window; I passed him, crossed<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150144"></xptr>over, and saw him carrying the coffee down the street; he put it into Bartlett's arms about two doors from the shop: I crossed and took Bartlett - I tried to take Hill, but he stooped down, and I missed him; he was stopped within a few yards.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Bartlett's Defence. I was merely passing along, and this young man asked me to give him a lift with the bag.</p>
               <p>CHARLES HERDSFIELD. Bartlett received it into his arms, and I laid hold of him - I had not seen them speak to each other, but he was standing still about two houses off.</p>
               <p>Hill put in a written Defence, stating that a man had employed him to carry the bag, and that he asked Bartlett to help it on his shoulder.</p>
               <p>HILL - <rs id="t18300415-342-verdict1852" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-342-verdict1852" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
